        <h2>You're Not Alone</h2>
        <p>Perimenopause affects roughly 1.5 million people each year in the US alone. Despite this, it's often not discussed openly, leaving many feeling isolated or confused about what's happening to their bodies.</p>
        <p>Understanding what's happening is the first step. Tracking your experience helps you take control. And remember — this is a transition, not a destination. Most symptoms improve or resolve after menopause.</p>
